{
  "info": {
    "name": "Athena Virus Scanner - Edge Cases & Breaking Scenarios",
    "description": "Comprehensive test suite for virus scanning functionality with edge cases, attack vectors, and performance validation.\n\n## Test Categories\n\n1. **Edge Cases**\n   - Boundary file sizes (10MB exact, 10MB+1)\n   - Network interruption mid-scan\n   - Slow connection timeouts\n   - Malformed content-type headers\n   - Concurrent large uploads\n\n2. **Breaking Scenarios**\n   - Network error retry bypass (P1 vulnerability)\n   - Infected file with connection failures\n   - Race conditions in scanning\n   - Resource exhaustion attacks\n\n3. **Security Validation**\n   - Nested archives (zip bombs)\n   - Polyglot files\n   - EICAR test virus detection\n   - Blocked file type circumvention\n\n4. **Performance Testing**\n   - Memory usage under load\n   - CPU usage during scanning\n   - Response time benchmarks\n   - Concurrent scan throughput\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n- `baseUrl` - API base URL (e.g., http://localhost:8080)\n- `access_token` - JWT access token\n- `clamav_address` - ClamAV address for health checks\n\n## Test Data Requirements\n\n- EICAR test file (standard antivirus test file)\n- 10MB test file (boundary condition)\n- 10MB+1 byte file (over boundary)\n- Large file for performance testing (100MB+)\n- Nested ZIP archive (zip bomb simulation)\n- Polyglot file (multiple valid formats)\n\n## Vulnerability Context\n\nThese tests validate the fix for a P1 vulnerability where infected files could bypass scanning when network errors occur during ClamAV communication. The original issue allowed:\n\n1. Network interruption → fallback mode triggered\n2. Infected file accepted without scan\n3. File processed and distributed\n\n**Fix**: Strict retry logic with proper error handling and mandatory scanning before processing.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "virus-scanner-tests"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "test_session_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "test_video_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "scan_attempts",
      "value": "0",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Edge Cases",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload Exactly 10MB File (Boundary)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate exactly 10MB of data",
                  "const tenMB = 10 * 1024 * 1024;",
                  "pm.environment.set('file_size_10mb', tenMB);",
                  "",
                  "// Log boundary condition test",
                  "console.log('Testing boundary condition: exactly 10MB file');",
                  "console.log('Expected: File should be accepted and scanned');",
                  "",
                  "// Set timestamp for unique filename",
                  "const timestamp = Date.now();",
                  "pm.environment.set('test_timestamp', timestamp);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 201 Created', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.test('Upload session created for 10MB file', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(response).to.have.property('success', true);",
                  "        pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property('session_id');",
                  "    });",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.test('File size accepted at boundary', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(response.data).to.have.property('total_chunks');",
                  "        pm.expect(response.data.total_chunks).to.be.above(0);",
                  "    });",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('test_session_id', response.data.session_id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('test_video_id', response.data.video_id);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"filename\": \"test-10mb-exact-{{test_timestamp}}.mp4\",\n  \"file_size\": {{file_size_10mb}},\n  \"chunk_size\": 5242880,\n  \"video_metadata\": {\n    \"title\": \"10MB Boundary Test\",\n    \"description\": \"Testing exact 10MB file size boundary\",\n    \"privacy\": \"private\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/uploads/initiate",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "uploads", "initiate"]
            }
          }
        },
